<font color="#FF0000">LIVING WITH IT</font><br>
<tt>Tue Jan 14 20:09:32 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
  I've been thinking about Viet Nam lately because I just hade my 26 year anniversity of my return on Jan. 1.           I came to the conclusion that a person has many lives in thier life time. I consider the Army as one of these lives. Viet Nam is a part of that life.                              I don't think I have a problem with it even though I think about it every day.                                           I'm content with my memories because I never did anything that I 'm ashamed of. I behaved like a soldier. I did the things a soldier has to do.                                   I remember every thing. The terror, friendship, jungle, V.C., N.V.A., P.F., A.R.V.N., dope, whores, diesel fumes, stand down, and Fun.                                          These things belong to me. And they belong to all those who experianced them. We are special because of them.         But now it's another Life. It's not my life now. And it's ok to think about it.                                                                                                                           FEZ
